Authorities in India and Bangladesh are on high alert as Cyclone Sidr, a powerful storm with winds up to 240 km/h, threatens the region.
Evacuations are underway in vulnerable coastal areas, with fears of significant loss of life.
The cyclone hit Bangladesh's southern coast, leaving devastation in its wake and forcing hundreds of thousands to flee.
International aid efforts are in motion, with Germany providing emergency relief funds.
The United States is also offering support and expressing sympathy for the victims.
As the storm weakens and moves northeast, the focus is on providing shelter, clean water, and medical assistance to those affected.
